1 AMEND House Committee Substitute for House Bill No. 2536, Page 5, Section 8.672, Line 40,
2 by inserting after all of said line the following:
3
4 "9. Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, any individual seeking to
5 access a public restroom on the house side of the Missouri capitol shall first present themselves
6 in person to the speaker of the house of representatives for physical inspection and verification
7 prior to entry to the public restroom. Such physical inspection of the individual seeking to
8 access a public restroom on the house side of the Missouri capitol shall be conducted in a
9 manner determined solely at the discretion of the speaker of the house of representatives, and no
10 individual seeking such access shall be permitted entry to the public restroom absent express
11 authorization. The speaker shall coordinate all physical inspection and verification processes
12 with the office of administration to establish and maintain a comprehensive system of
13 registration, identification, tracking, and continuous monitoring of all individuals seeking access
14 to such a public restroom, including the creation and retention of permanent records of those
15 individuals who are granted access."; and
16
17 Further amend said bill by amending the title, enacting clause, and intersectional references
18 accordingly.
